beer.beer_description:
This nitro stout is brewed using a blend of pale, crystal and roasted grains. Whirlpool hop additions supply a layer of spice, while vanilla, lactose, molasses and over thirty kilos of Elementary Coffee perk up the pint. 
It pours silky smooth with velvet head. Expect aromas of tiramisu and treacle, with lifted notes of macadamia. The palate shows sweet coffee, liquorice bullets and a fine acidity. Choc-cherry goes long on the finish.
